For {= integrity_case =}+ bounded local-search integrity or abuse-defense cases, provide {= independent_case_source =}+ independent public source pages per case, with each source backed by {= url =}+ URL. Each case should name a specific affected local surface, abuse mechanism, and `defensive_signal` within one public incident, regulator/court action, research or measurement finding, threat-analysis finding, or defensive source-integrity risk on a location-bound local search, Maps, Business Profile, local listing/directory, local business review, local service marketplace, local travel or hospitality listing, or local-intent AI/search-answer surface.

The purpose is practitioner-useful public evidence for defensive local-search integrity work, not a bibliography of platform policies, broad help pages, SEO advice, complaint optimization, abuse methods, legal conclusions, monitoring-product guidance, outreach, contact enrichment, or lead generation.

A valid `integrity_case` is narrower than a general abuse category, anchored by independent public field evidence, and tied by the cited page to a bounded local-place, local-service, local-listing, local-business-review, or local-intent search/answer discovery unit. It must also include a case-specific `defensive_signal`: a source-stated detection, verification, reporting, recourse, removal, enforcement, measurement, owner-protection, consumer-warning, or source-integrity lesson that a local operator, platform, regulator, researcher, or defender could actually use. For example, "fake reviews" is too broad by itself, while a local-business review-suppression settlement with a source-stated owner/reviewer protection signal, fake Maps or Business Profile listing lawsuit with real-world-location verification implications, local-service lead-diversion incident with a stated reporting or redressal implication, place-profile review-bombing incident pattern with a stated detection/removal signal, hijacked or spoofed local listing pattern with an owner-verification signal, fake local support-number poisoning case with a source-integrity warning signal, or research-measured AI-generated review risk in local service categories with a measurement/detection signal can be a distinct case when independent source evidence supports that bounded surface, finding, and signal. One public proceeding, regulator action, lawsuit, news-reported incident, or research/measurement report normally counts as one `integrity_case` even when it describes several tactics, harms, metrics, parties, or example passages; those details can describe the case, but they should not become separate cases unless a separate affected local surface, separate public finding, and separate defensive signal remain visible. Generic consumer-product reviews, app-store reviews, ecommerce marketplace reviews, national brand endorsement cases, broad AI review-generation issues, broad SEO/search spam, and general online reputation topics are outside the root case universe unless the cited passage ties them to local business, place, local service, local listing, or local-intent discovery. A valid independent source page is published or authored by a regulator, court, researcher, nonprofit, reputable news outlet, public-interest organization, security/threat-research organization, trade-research organization, or comparable source that is independent of the affected platform or source ecosystem. Platform-owned help, policy, trust/safety, transparency, blog, press, reporting, and enforcement pages do not establish a case here, even when they include metrics or examples. The cited page itself must visibly carry enough content to evaluate the claimed case, defensive signal, and independent source. Pages can mention manipulation, scams, fake reviews, fake listings, reporting routes, or AI/search poisoning only to prohibit, report, document, respond to, or analyze them at a high level. Pages dominated by operational abuse methods, evasion, fake review or fake listing creation, competitor takedown strategy, ranking advice, legal or compliance advice, procurement or supplier recommendations, monitoring-product guidance, outreach, contact enrichment, lead scoring, or lead-generation workflows are outside the evidence scope.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly tie to the claimed `integrity_case` on the claimed `abuse_surface` through independent public observation, incident, research, regulator/court, news, threat-analysis, measurement, or defensive-risk evidence, and it must show both why that case belongs to a local-place, local-service, local-listing, local-business-review, or local-intent search/answer surface rather than a generic product, ecommerce, app-store, broad review, or generic SEO/search-spam surface and why the claimed case is a bounded incident, proceeding, finding, or measurement unit rather than one slice of a broader source page.
- The page must clearly identify the claimed independent source page: the source owner should be the page's publisher, authoring organization, court/regulator, news outlet, research organization, public-interest organization, threat-research organization, or comparable public source owner, and the source page should be the concrete article, report, case page, court/regulator page, research page, or named section being cited rather than a broad source family.
- The page must state a source-local case signal for the claimed case: who or what local business, place, local service, local listing, local review surface, local-intent result, local-intent answer, affected incident/proceeding, research corpus, measured category, or bounded finding was observed, measured, reported, alleged, adjudicated, researched, affected, exploited, or made defensively relevant. Generic policy indexes, generic help pages, broad SEO advice, platform transparency reports, marketing pages, broad explainers about fake reviews or spam, and pages that only prove a public source page exists are not enough unless the cited passage carries this concrete independent local case signal.
- The page must support the claimed `defensive_signal` with source-stated content: what detection, verification, reporting, recourse, removal, enforcement, measurement, owner-protection, consumer-warning, or source-integrity lesson follows from this specific local case. A penalty, lawsuit, bad-review story, or broad fake-listing topic is not enough unless the cited passage makes the defensive signal visible.
